      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To find the relative major from a minor key, you move up a minor third (three semitones) on the circle of fifths. Ebony major (Eb Major) is actually a major key, but if you mean Eb minor, its relative major is G minor's relative major, which is Bb Major. In general, the relative major shares the same key signature and moves from the relative minor up a minor third.",
