    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Starting from C minor, which is in the key signature of C minor, you move up a minor third (three semitones) to find its relative major. Moving up three steps from C on the circle of fifths takes you to Eb Major. This works because the relative major and minor share the exact same key signature. Think of it as finding the major key with the same notes, just with a different root.",
      "source": "target",
